Configuring Git in Command-Line
*******************************

git help

git config --global user.name "IT Support"			//Name
git config --global user.email "itsupport@maxxion.com"	//Email
git config --global color.ui "auto"				//Colour
git config --global core.editor "vim"				//Editor


Steps for file Pushing & Committing
***********************************

cd /home/hoshin/sample_project						//enter the project location
git init											//Initialize Git
git add .											// "." implies all files in that directory.
git status										//Initiat commit: Committed files.
git commit -m "First all from sample_project"			//Initializing committed files to git. "First all from sample_project" is just a description.
git status										//The cchanged are get committed.
git remote add origin https://github.com/Maxxion/test.git	//Settting the location in Git for pushing.
git remote -v										//To know the location.
git push origin master								//Pushing the committed files to Git Respository named "test". It promtps Username & Password: Maxxion & =s0j|K?}+I


Steps to Pull an entire Project to a server
*******************************************

ssh -p 69 itsupport@107.21.97.50
its@test.dev
sudo su -
su - hoshin
git config --global user.name "hoshin"
git config --global user.email "itsupport@maxxion.com"
git config --global color.ui "auto"
git config --global core.editor "vim"

git init
cd ~/											//Go to the location where you want the project to be located.
git remote add origin https://github.com/Maxxion/test.git
git remote -v
git pull origin master

	OR get the same using clone

git init
cd ~/											//Go to the location where you want the project to be located.
git remote add origin https://github.com/Maxxion/tgit pull origin masterest.git
git remote -v
git clone https://github.com/Maxxion/test.git

